Diverse groups, including artisans, community leaders and the downtrodden have promised to support the All Progressive Grand Alliance (APGA), House of Representatives candidate, Idemili North/South Federal Constituency, Ikenna Obumneme Iyiegbu in the forthcoming 2023 general elections. This was made known at an event held in Idemili North Local Government Area when the popular youth philanthropist and politician, Iyiegbu met with the people of the area. A community leader, Paschal Onyeka who spoke on behalf of the people stated that with what Ikenna Iyiegbu has done for them in his own capacity as a private businessman, we know when he gets there he will do more. “We, therefore, charged him to stand firm on his aspiration as we are solidly behind you for the House of Representatives position in 2023, to enable you to have a robust network to more for us. In response,  Iyiegbu expressed delight to be with them and listen to them as they show appreciation for the little I have done for them. “Events like this give me the courage to do more, and I am happy to see them smile”. On the call for a political office, “I believe that only God gives power, and in the end, He will show forth his might for us in my aspiration. “I do not take this massive support for granted, as I assure my people that I will run for the Idemili North and South Federal Constituency seat in the House of Representatives in 2023, and win convincingly with their massive support”, he added.